# backend-review-checklist

Full version: `.claude/agents/backend-reviewer.md`.

Check, in order of severity:
1. **Non-negotiable:** no path where an LLM call's output flows directly into a reward/points/value number shown to a user without deterministic calculation in between. Flag this regardless of confidence elsewhere.
2. New code lives in the right one of the five backend engines (Reward Knowledge / Valuation / Optimization / Simulation / AI Reasoning Layer) — no calculation logic inside the AI Reasoning Layer's code path.
3. No premature microservice/queue/agent-framework for something a plain function could do (see `codebase-design.mdc`).
4. Calculation code (the four deterministic engines) has tests with concrete golden values and boundary cases (see `tdd.mdc`) — flag missing coverage.
5. New schema fields/rules are consistent with `docs/architecture/db-schema-v1.md`, not silently diverging from it.
